        {
            "_id": "LNIDuf4K5NOmol4v",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Petty Whispers",
            "sort": 1100000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The mocking chorus adopts the voices of its enemies, spreading lies and jeers among would-be allies and tearing apart trusted friends. Creatures in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:60] of the mocking chorus must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:37] save. The mocking chorus can't use petty whispers again for 1 minute.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune for 1 day.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> As failure, but the creature takes half damage and is not @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Confused].</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[12d10[mental]] damage and is confused for 1 minute. It can attempt a new save at the end of each of its turns to end the confusion.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[15d10[mental]] damage and is confused for 1 minute, with no save to end early.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
